review_blob: Had this on tap at the Dunedin House of Beer, this was a great well balanced Imp IPA. This is a dangerous beer, which gives little hint that it is a 10% IPA. Abslutely delicious!
beer_name: Great Divide Anniversary Wood Aged Double IPA

review_blob: This is one of the best of this years summer seasonals! Great color, an aroma of wonderful fresh hops, nice head with good lacing, a very well balanced easily drinkable beer with just the right amount of bitterness.
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Sumpin Ale

review_blob: While this is indeed a good beer, I feel the 60 Minute is a bit over rated, and I tend to rate higher than most members. I buy and enjoy this beer, but generally prefer the beers from Bells Brewery.

This is a great red. Hold a glass of Retro Red up into the Suna nd see for yourself the beautiful Ruby red color of a true red ale. With a fluffy white head and just the right amount of bitterness, this beer is enjoyed by all.
This is a big American DIPA that does a fair job of hiding its 10% ABV. I much prefer this more balanced hopheads delight over the more malty and higher IBU Avery Maharaja.
This is one of my favorite porters, this is a rich creamy smooth porter, a true classic. The Famous Taddy Porter is a style defining beer.
This is a wonderful chocolate stout. The aroma is of a deep rich chocolate, the head is creamy. Highly recommend adding 2 oz. ofLindemans Framboise for a delicious after dinner drink.
This is the perfect IPA; the bitterness is perfectly balanced with a creamy malt, and the 7% ABV is just right for an IPA.
This is a great ale, with a wonderful finish, this is a beer I could drink all night long.

beer_brewer_name: Magners GB / Shepton Mallet Cider Mill (C&C; Group)
review_blob: This is a fine dry cider. Plenty of tart apple flavor without the excess sugar many ciders exhibit. If judged strictly as a cider, without comparison to beer, then this would score higher.
Not as sweet as some ciders, but not a dry cider either. It was enjoyed, but Dry Blackthorn is much preferred.
